It was a massive struggle but the Lions found enough resolve to beat the Cheetahs by 28-25 in Bloemfontein on Saturday. The skill levels in this arm-wrestle was shockingly poor as both sides never gained any fluency. In the end it was a moment of magic from substitute Ross Cronje that led to Rohan Janse van Rensburg&#8217;s second and winning try. Full report to follow shortly. Point scorers: Lions 28 (6) &#8211; Tries: Rohan Janse van Rensburg (2), penalty try (7 points). Conversion: Elton Jantjies. Penalties: Jantjies (3). Cheetahs 25 (6) &#8211; Try: Raymond Rhule. Conversion: Fred Zeilinga. Penalties: Zeilinga (6). Tweets by TheCitizenSport For more sport your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.